# Workflow Preferences

## General
- Use consistent indentation (4 spaces)
- Follow project-specific coding standards
- Maintain clear and descriptive commit messages
- Regular code reviews and pair programming when appropriate

## Development Flow
- Create feature branches for new work
- Write tests before implementing features (TDD approach)
- Regular commits with meaningful messages
- Pull requests for code review before merging

## Documentation
- Keep documentation up to date
- Include README files for major components
- Document complex algorithms and business logic
- Maintain clear API documentation

## Code Organization
- Modular and reusable components
- Clear separation of concerns
- Consistent file and directory structure
- Meaningful naming conventions



